<concept id="concept_E8D43EB4494E41D2AB42D4A89396D1AB"
                    xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Communication</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>There are components in <ph conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                        />, for example Apache Storm, that require a Fully Qualified Domain Name (FQDN) that absolutely and uniquely identifies the corresponding host machine in your <ph
                                        conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                /> environment. </p>
            <p>Before installing <ph conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    />, it is therefore required to define the mapping of IP addresses, host names, and FQDNs. You can either specify the DNS, or you can map your IP addresses in the <codeph>/etc/hosts</codeph> file on your <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> host.</p>
            <p>Example configuration in the <codeph>/etc/hosts</codeph> file:</p>
            <codeblock>127.0.0.1 localhost
192.168.10.4 monasca.cmm monasca
192.168.10.5 openstack.cmm openstack</codeblock>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
